\begin_layout Section
Setting up
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The “GM-Octo-2023” session was designed as a “demonstration” of the “Game
 Master” software, and is adapted to the configuration of the monitors of
 the electroacoustic studio of the Saint-Etienne conservatory (an octophony
 in the form of 4 pairs), but it must be able to work on any configuration.
 Compared to the “Octo” session previously distributed, this one brings
 new play modes and space modes for certain groups, and deserves a new listen.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We assume of course that version 6.75 (or later) of REAPER is correctly installed
 on your machine.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The contents of the “GM-Octo” folder are as follows.
 First, everything that is essential to be immediately operational, in the
 sense that it is not necessary to install the “GameMaster” on your machine,
 as described in Doc § 1.3:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Audio This directory contains the different items used by this specific
 session.
 These could be audio files (as it turns out, there aren't any here), or
 files of another type, such as image files or videos.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Data This directory contains a subdirectory, named “WAVES”, which itself
 contains the audio files specific to this GameMaster session, the nomenclature
 of which is described in Doc § 1.5.
 These sounds have been placed under a free license by their creators, Gilles
 Roussi (clips 2100 to 2167), Diego Losa (2501 to 2525), Francis Valéry
 (3100 to 3156), Alain Girardot (3200 to 3281) and Jean-Jacques Girardot
 ( 3300 to 3353).
 May they all be warmly thanked.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Effects This directory contains the “GameMaster” directory described in
 Doc § 1.3.2, which, placed in the session itself, allows you to work without
 additional installation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
GM-Octo.RPP is the REAPER file describing the session.
 You can double-click it to start this session.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
ReaScripts This directory contains the auxiliary script “GMAuxiliary.eel”.
 It is not necessary for the session to function properly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Some of the files contained in “Effects” are there for informational purposes
 only, and offer different example scripts.
 They are not useful for the session.
 The proposed session is the result of a “Game Master integrated into the
 project” installation as described in Doc § 1.3.2.1.
\end_layout

