\begin_layout Section
Launch
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The work described here must be done only once, during a new installation
 of GameMaster on your machine.
 The reason for this is that you need to create an initial file of presets
 adapted to your machine, for the GameMaster when it is integrated into
 a project.
 Here is the algorithm to use from the demo session, named “GM-Octo”.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If previous versions of the GM had been installed, it may be necessary to
 delete the old presets, as they are no longer compatible, or even to delete
 the backup file of the GM presets.
 To do this, go to the “rrR” (REAPER resources directory), go down to “presets”,
 and delete (or move, or rename) the files named “js-GameMaster_GamePlayer_jsfx.i
ni” or “js-_Project__GamePlayer_jsfx.
 ini”.
 Also delete, or set aside, the previous version of Game Master (located
 in “<rrR>/Effects”, probably under the name “Game-Master” or equivalent).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Double click on the “GM-Octo.RPP” file.
 This starts the session, and displays the “GameMaster” window.
 If this window does not appear immediately, click on the (green) “FX” box
 of track “1”, named “GAME PLAYER”.
 You should get on your screen something similar to the image 
