\begin_layout Standard
Take the time to listen to each group of sounds for a few minutes.
 Before moving from one group to another, you can interrupt and then reactivate
 sound generation by clicking “Play Control ➯ Auto-Play”.
 Note that “Play Control ➯ Stop Play” immediately interrupts the sounds
 in progress.
 Adjust the output volume (“Parameters A ➯ Vol.
 Glob.”) to your liking.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Some experiments to do:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
change the number of generators (“Parameters A ➯ Generators #”).
 Allow time for this new new value to stabilize.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
modify the reading/looping ratio: “Parameters A ➯ Read/Loop”.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
change the duration of loop rendering: “Parameters A ➯ Loop Dur.”.
 Between 4 and 200 seconds, the influence on the resulting mix is astonishing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
change the basic fade-in duration of loops: “Parameters A ➯ Gr.
 Fade.
 In”, going from minimum to maximum, will allow you to obtain a number of
 different attacks which fundamentally change the sound.
 Changes to the fade-out “Parameters A ➯ Gr.
 Fade.
 Out” will also give you interesting results.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
change the playback speed of clips, using “Parameters A ➯ Contin.R”.
 This parameter acts in real time on the readers.
 Speeds below 1 (0.2 to 0.8) often give interesting timbres.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
And also...
 The “Scheduler” offers three simple tasks: random changes in Volume, number
 of generators, and group played.
 We start them by left-clicking on “Scheduler ➯ Vol.
 Change”, “Scheduler ➯ Gen.
 Change” and “Scheduler ➯ Grp.
 Change”, and we stop them by right-clicking on these same buttons.
 To modify the framing of these values, use the “Parameters B” module placed
 in the “Studio B” tab.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
And again...
 Everything that has been played so far is recorded – or almost.
 The “Play Log” (“Studio B” tab) will allow you to listen identically to
 all the sounds produced...
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Stop auto-play (“Play Log ➯ Auto-Play”) and recording (right-click “Play
 Log ➯ Recording\SpecialChar menuseparator
Stop”).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Choose “Play Log ➯ Stopped\SpecialChar menuseparator
Replay”.
 The replayer replays the session at speed “1”.
 It is possible to position yourself at any moment of the session (using
 the “Virt.Time” slider).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A complete chapter of the manual is devoted to describing all the possibilities
 of the replayer.
 Discover them!
\end_layout

